section.section:
The fine for each civil violation of the Erosion and Sediment Control Ordinance of Calvert County is:
$250 for the first violation;
$500 for the second violation;
$750 for the third violation; and
$1,000 for each violation in excess of three.

text.section:
The citation shall be on a form adopted by the Board of County Commissioners of Calvert County, which shall include:
The date of issuance of the citation;
The name and address of the person charged;
The section number of the Erosion and Sediment Control Ordinance that has been violated;
The nature of the violation;
The place where and time when the violation occurred;
The amount of the civil fine assessed;
The manner, location, and time period in which the fine is to be paid;
Where applicable, the notice that each day of continued violation thereafter shall be deemed a separate violation subject to additional citation;
The name, business address, and telephone number of the county official cognizant of the case; and
The person's right to elect to stand trial for the violation, and instructions and timing necessary for this right to stand trial.
